============================================================
SEQUENTIAL UPDATING WITH VFE TRACKING
============================================================
Scenario: Weather estimation over multiple days using PyMDP
- Hidden state: Weather (Sunny=0, Rainy=1)
- Observation: Umbrella usage (No=0, Yes=1)
- Track VFE evolution over sequential updates

Initial prior D: [0.7 0.3] → ['Sunny', 'Rainy']

Observation model A (P(umbrella | weather)):
              Sunny  Rainy
No umbrella:   0.9    0.2
Umbrella:      0.1    0.8

Sequential VFE-based updating:
Day  Obs         Prior → Posterior           VFE    Info Gain  Certainty
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1   Umbrella   [0.7 0.3] → [0.22580645 0.77419355]   1.171    0.478    0.774
 2   Umbrella   [0.22580645 0.77419355] → [0.03517588 0.96482412]   0.443    0.147    0.965
 3   No umbrella [0.03517588 0.96482412] → [0.1409396 0.8590604]   1.493    0.096    0.859
 4   Umbrella   [0.1409396 0.8590604] → [0.02009569 0.97990431]   0.355    0.090    0.980
 5   No umbrella [0.02009569 0.97990431] → [0.08448815 0.91551185]   1.541    0.059    0.916

VFE Evolution Analysis:
- Lower VFE indicates better model fit to observations
- VFE changes reflect surprise at each observation
  Day 1: Umbrella → VFE=1.171 (High surprise)
  Day 2: Umbrella → VFE=0.443 (Low surprise)
  Day 3: No umbrella → VFE=1.493 (High surprise)
  Day 4: Umbrella → VFE=0.355 (Low surprise)
  Day 5: No umbrella → VFE=1.541 (High surprise)

