✅ COMPREHENSIVE TAKEAWAYS: VFE-BASED BAYESIAN INFERENCE WITH PYMDP
================================================================================
🎉 ALL PYMDP VALIDATIONS PASSED - Educational VFE implementations verified!

🧮 MATHEMATICAL FOUNDATIONS:
1. VFE = Complexity - Accuracy = KL(q||p) - E_q[ln P(o|s)]
2. PyMDP minimizes VFE to perform optimal Bayesian inference
3. Complexity (KL divergence) measures departure from prior beliefs
4. Accuracy measures how well the model explains observations
5. Lower VFE indicates better model fit to data

⚡ COMPUTATIONAL INSIGHTS:
6. Sequential updates: posterior becomes next prior, VFE tracks surprise
7. Information gain = reduction in uncertainty from observations
8. VFE provides principled measure of model uncertainty and surprise
9. Educational implementations match PyMDP exactly (validated)

🔬 PyMDP Methods Demonstrated & Validated:
- pymdp.inference.update_posterior_states() for state inference
- pymdp.agent.Agent() for high-level inference interface
- pymdp.maths.kl_div() for complexity calculations
- pymdp.maths.entropy() for information analysis
- pymdp.utils.obj_array_* for proper model structure
- All educational VFE calculations validated against PyMDP

